        "english": ["the father, having been ordered, saw the son at once"],
        "explanation": "*vidit* = he saw (perfect, *video*). *pater iussus* = the father having been ordered (PPP of *iubeo*, masc. sg. nom.). *filium* = the son (accusative). *statim* = at once.",
    },
    {
        "latin": "noli gladium tenere, filia.",
        "english": ["don't hold the sword, daughter"],
        "explanation": "*noli* = don't (*noli* + infinitive = negative command). *gladium tenere* = to hold the sword. *filia* = daughter (vocative).",
    },
    {
        "latin": "deus, enim, omnes naves habebat et milites vix apparebant.",
        "english": ["for the god was having all the ships and the soldiers were scarcely appearing"],
        "explanation": "*enim* = for (placed second in the clause). *deus* = the god. *omnes naves habebat* = was having all the ships (imperfect, *habeo*). *et* = and. *milites* = the soldiers. *vix apparebant* = were scarcely appearing (imperfect, *appareo*).",
    },
    {
        "latin": "rex milites igitur liberavit quod pater ei persuaserat.",
        "english": ["the king therefore freed the soldiers because the father had persuaded him"],
        "explanation": "*rex* = the king. *milites igitur liberavit* = therefore freed the soldiers (perfect, *libero*). *quod* = because. *pater* = the father. *ei persuaserat* = had persuaded him (pluperfect, *persuadeo*; *ei* = dative).",
    },
    {
        "latin": "postquam deus ex ingenti silva apparuit, milites perterriti erant.",
        "english": ["after the god appeared from the huge wood, the soldiers were terrified"],
        "explanation": "*postquam* = after. *deus ex ingenti silva apparuit* = the god appeared from the huge wood (perfect, *appareo*). *milites* = the soldiers. *perterriti erant* = were terrified (imperfect of *esse* + PPP; note *perterriti* agrees with *milites*, masc. pl.).",
    },
]

PARSE_TRANSLATE_2ND = [
    {"form":"videt",        "tense":"present",    "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she sees"},
    {"form":"habent",       "tense":"present",    "person":"3rd","number":"plural",  "translation":"they have"},
    {"form":"tenet",        "tense":"present",    "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she holds"},
    {"form":"tenebat",      "tense":"imperfect",  "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she was holding"},
    {"form":"persuadebant", "tense":"imperfect",  "person":"3rd","number":"plural",  "translation":"they were persuading"},
    {"form":"videbit",      "tense":"future",     "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she will see"},
    {"form":"apparebunt",   "tense":"future",     "person":"3rd","number":"plural",  "translation":"they will appear"},
    {"form":"vidit",        "tense":"perfect",    "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she saw"},
    {"form":"habuerunt",    "tense":"perfect",    "person":"3rd","number":"plural",  "translation":"they had"},
    {"form":"persuasit",    "tense":"perfect",    "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she persuaded"},
    {"form":"apparuit",     "tense":"perfect",    "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she appeared"},
    {"form":"viderat",      "tense":"pluperfect", "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she had seen"},
    {"form":"habuerat",     "tense":"pluperfect", "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she had had"},
    {"form":"tenuerat",     "tense":"pluperfect", "person":"3rd","number":"singular","translation":"he/she had held"},
]

