        "pass_mark":80,
        "screens":[{
            "heading":"The 3rd Conjugation",
            "body":"3rd conjugation verbs are recognisable by their infinitive, which ends in *-ere* (with a short *-e-*, unlike the 2nd conjugation *-ere* with a long *-e-*).\n\nThe 'I' form always ends in *-o*:\n\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0*dico* = I say\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0*duco* = I lead\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0*peto* = I seek\n\nNote: a small group of 3rd conjugation verbs have *-io* in the 'I' form (e.g. *facio* = I make, *accipio* = I receive). They follow the same pattern as all other 3rd conjugation verbs \u2014 just memorise the principal parts for each verb.",
        }],
        "content":{"verbs":VERBS_3RD_TOP150, "mode":"meanings"},
    },
    {
        "id":39, "node":3, "node_title":"3rd Conjugation",
