        "type":"translate_form",
        "sell":"This set teaches you all six present tense endings for 3rd conjugation verbs.",
        "pass_mark":80,
        "screens":[{
            "heading":"3rd Conjugation: Present Tense Endings",
            "body":"The person endings for 3rd conjugation verbs are **o / s / t / mus / tis / nt** — the same set as all conjugations.\n\nThe difference is the connecting vowel between stem and ending: *-i-* for most forms, and *-u-* before *-nt* (they).",
            "table":[
                {"conjugation":"I",            "infinitive_ending":"-o",   "example":"dico",    "ep":[["dic",""],["o","blue"]]},
                {"conjugation":"you (sg)",      "infinitive_ending":"-s",   "example":"dicis",   "ep":[["dic",""],["i","coral"],["s","blue"]]},
                {"conjugation":"he / she / it", "infinitive_ending":"-t",   "example":"dicit",   "ep":[["dic",""],["i","coral"],["t","blue"]]},
                {"conjugation":"we",            "infinitive_ending":"-mus", "example":"dicimus", "ep":[["dic",""],["i","coral"],["mus","blue"]]},
